PropertyPackage.ComponentDescription: Property Package that uses the Soave-Redlich-Kwong Cubic Equation of State. Recommended for use with hydrocarbons and non-condensables.
Uses NRTL (Non-Random Two-Liquid) model to calculate liquid-phase activity coefficients.
Uses UNIQUAC model to calculate liquid-phase activity coefficients.
Soave-Redlich-Kwong EOS with T/P-dependent Interaction Parameters

Liquid phase Activity Coefficients are calculated by the Modified UNIFAC (Dortmund) method. Enthalpies, Entropies and Heat Capacities (both phases) are calculated by the Lee-Kesler method. The remaining properties, including vapor phase Fugacity Coefficients (optionally), are calculated using the Peng-Robinson EOS.
